CONTEXT
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The RMS workflow currently has `messages: list` in RMSState as a
plain (non-channel) field. Nodes that emit AIMessages return
`{"messages": messages + [ai_message]}`, manually appending.

This causes the chat_controller's on_chain_end handler to surface
ALL accumulated messages from state — including ones from previous
turns — every time a node ends. The user sees old messages echoed
back in each new response.

The standard LangGraph pattern is to use the `add_messages` channel
annotation. With it, nodes return only the NEW message, and LangGraph
itself appends to the accumulated state. Reads in chat_controller's
on_chain_end still get a full message list, but each individual
node's `output["messages"]` (the value returned by the node) contains
only the new messages from that node.

This task fixes RMS only. HRMS and MRR will adopt the same pattern
in Tasks 4.3 and 4.4.

